\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating test placeholders**\\n\\nI’m considering whether we should remove the placeholder text \\\"This is just a placeholder.\\\" It might not be the best for a scaffold-only test, especially because it can attract criticism in a review. Since we now have a meaningful test, the existing placeholder could be seen as unnecessary noise. However, leaving it as is might be acceptable. Still, I wonder if scaffold-only tests should be deleted or if they could serve as a baseline.\\n\\n**Considering test deletions**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether removing the scaffold-only tests might have any effects. While all existing tests pass, deleting the placeholder could clean up the code, even if they're not contributing meaningfully. Still, I need to keep the task focus on adding or refining tests rather than broadening the scope. Plus, I need to ensure that we adhere to the requirement that all top-level test classes must be public. There are also concerns regarding loading nested classes in Native Image, and I need to double-check the details on that.\\n\\n**Examining dynamic library calls**\\n\\nI'm analyzing how the library calls are dynamic, particularly since the string used in the test isn't a constant at build time, possibly coming from Class.getName(). The agent likely generates reflection metadata for loading classes. I believe class metadata registration is necessary for reflection, and this will involve registering the provider using `providerFactory.registerProvider(provider)`, which would allow for reflective instantiation later. There's a potential compile issue because the `resteasy-core` dependency might not include `jakarta.annotation-api`, and I'm also considering Java 11 source compatibility.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_073818f911defdc20169fe2dd351d4819e892e9b583b9ba962\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_i3ghEUpDKz4Uwp1qogPbAzColUD2xipd_IxrXZ1xo6vitEA6wSC99MJKxymtCrVXbox6eURek