codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n../3312-20a114be/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n../3312-20a114be/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:266:- For Forge: a predefined strategy name selecting agent + workflow + prompts.\n../3312-20a114be/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:314:    task.setDescription(\"Generates a per-class dynamic-access coverage report for matching coordinates\")\n../3312-20a114be/docs/assets/readme/button-new-library.svg:10:      .surface { fill: none; stroke: #3b4858; }\n../3312-20a114be/docs/assets/readme/button-new-library.svg:20:  <image href=\"data:image/png;base64,\" x=\"15\" y=\"12\" width=\"45\" height=\"50\" />\n../3312-20a114be/docs/assets/readme/button-update-metadata.svg:10:      .surface { fill: none; stroke: #3b4858; }\n../3312-20a114be/docs/assets/readme/button-update-metadata.svg:20:  <image href=\"data:image/png;base64,\" x=\"15\" y=\"12\" width=\"45\" height=\"50\" />\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:25:- Python 3 and the tooling required by the agent strategy you plan to run.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:55:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:77:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5`.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:102:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:122:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `basic_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` (Pi agent).\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:198:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:215:  [--strategy-name NAME] \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:232:  - `strategy`: strategy name matching an entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:268:Agents are registered via `Agent.register(...)` and selected per-strategy through the `agent` field in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Supported agents:\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:270:- `pi` — default for the shipped strategies. Driven through `pi --mode rpc` by `PiAgent` (`ai_workflows/agents/pi_agent.py`). Per-turn transcripts are written to `logs/pi-<action>-<library>-<timestamp>.log` in this repository (see `utility_scripts/pi_logs.py`). Pi session files are stored under Pi's default session directory (`--session-dir` may override it via `PiRpcClient`). Select with strategy entries whose `agent` is `\"pi\"`; set `\"provider\": \"openrouter\"` to route through OpenRouter.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:280:When a strategy configures `persistent-instructions`, these logs record whether\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:295:      strategy_name=\"basic_iterative\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:325:  - `strategy` validates strategy config files using `schemas/strategy_schema.json`:\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:327:    python3 utility_scripts/schema_validator.py strategy strategies/predefined_strategies.json\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:344:The project uses registry-based workflow and agent abstractions. Each workflow strategy is a Python class that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy` and is registered via a decorator. Agents are registered in the same way via `Agent.register(...)`. Strategies are configured through `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, which defines the workflow, agent, model, optional provider, prompts, optional persistent instructions, and parameters for each strategy.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:348:#### Adding a variant of an existing strategy (different model or parameters)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:350:If you want to run an existing workflow with a different model or tuned parameters, add a new entry to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Reuse the same `workflow` and `agent` as the base strategy, and differentiate by appending a space and a descriptor to the name:\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:355:  \"description\": \"Iterative strategy with higher iteration limits\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:374:The strategy name is just a lookup key for the JSON entry. The workflow and agent implementations are resolved from the `workflow` and `agent` fields, so `basic_iterative aggressive` can still point at the `basic_iterative` workflow without any code changes.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:376:For coding agents that support selecting an LLM backend separately from the model identifier, add a top-level `provider` field to the strategy entry. For example, Pi strategies that should run through OpenRouter can set `\"provider\": \"openrouter\"`.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:378:For different prompt behavior, create new prompt template files under `prompt_templates/` and reference them in the new strategy entry. Ensure that the context given to strategy workflows has prompt template placeholders. Prompt templates support Python string formatting with context variables (e.g., `{library}`, `{new_version}`) that are substituted at run time from the workflow context. Be sure that the workflow context contains placeholder keys.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:390:1. **Add a strategy entry** to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` with the matching workflow, agent, prompts, and parameters.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:392:2. **Create a new strategy class** in `ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/` that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy`:\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:394:   from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.workflow_strategy import WorkflowStrategy\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:396:   @WorkflowStrategy.register(\"my_new_strategy\")\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:398:       \"\"\"Description of the new strategy.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:404:           # Implement strategy-specific workflow logic\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:407:`register` parameter is the workflow implementation name referenced by the strategy config's `workflow` field.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:411:   from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.my_new_strategy import MyNewStrategy\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:414:Importing the new module in `__init__.py` triggers the `@WorkflowStrategy.register` decorator, which adds the strategy to the internal registry so it can be looked up at run time.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:420:If the library has no dynamic access, the workflow falls back to the standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:424:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:461:  --strategy-name dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4 \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:472:  --strategy-name dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4 \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:483:  python3 ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:491:  python3 complete_pipelines/fix_javac_create_pr.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]\n../3312-20a114be/forge/DEVELOPING.md:493:  python3 complete_pipelines/add_new_library_support_create_pr.py --coordinates <coordinates> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]\n../3312-20a114be/forge/AGENTS.md:29:- Don't duplicate helpers for path resolution, strategy loading, metrics writing, source-context preparation, style checks, or GitHub/Git utilities without first checking the existing shared modules.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/AGENTS.md:40:- `ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/`: reusable workflow strategy implementations. Put iteration logic, workflow decision-making, and prompt sequencing here.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/AGENTS.md:45:- `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`: declarative workflow configuration such as strategy names, prompt files, parameters, model, and agent selection.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:391:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs javac_iterative to fix compilation, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:435:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:475:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs java_run_iterative to fix runtime failures, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:533:    \"description\": \"Pi bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:552:    \"description\": \"Codex bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:571:    \"description\": \"Pi graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:591:    \"description\": \"Codex graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:611:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:634:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement using gpt-5.5.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:657:    \"description\": \"Composite Codex strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:680:    \"description\": \"Composite Codex strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement using gpt-5.5.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:759:    \"description\": \"Library-update strategy: skips primary workflow, directly runs dynamic-access coverage improvement on existing tests.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:778:    \"description\": \"Library-update bulk dynamic-access strategy: runs only the optimistic full-report workflow against existing tests, without per-class refinement.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:798:    \"description\": \"Library-update composite strategy: bulk dynamic-access coverage in one broad pass first, then per-class iterative refinement of any stragglers. Mirrors the iterative library-update strategy but starts with a faster bulk pass.\",\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py:13:    [--strategy-name \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"] \\\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:108:    strategy_name = metrics_entry.get(\"strategy_name\", \"\")\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:109:    model_display_name = get_model_display_name(strategy_name)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:110:    agent_name = get_agent_name(strategy_name)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:142:- Strategy: {strategy_name}\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:150:- Iterations: {iterations}\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:13:      [--strategy-name <name>] [--reachability-metadata-path <path>]\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:57:from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.workflow_strategy import RUN_STATUS_CHUNK_READY, RUN_STATUS_FAILURE\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:107:from utility_scripts.strategy_loader import load_strategy_by_name, require_strategy_by_name\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:255:    strategy_name: str | None = None\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:312:    strategy_name: str | None\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:2511:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:2541:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:2553:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/forge_metadata.py:2580:            strategy_na