ess coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n../3312-20a114be/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:6:from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.workflow_strategy import RUN_STATUS_FAILURE, RUN_STATUS_SUCCESS, WorkflowStrategy\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:41:└─────────────────┘         │                       │ maxIterations reached?       │────────────────────────────────────┘\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:59:    \"\"\"Shared iterative fix strategy for javac compilation and java runtime test failures.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:64:    def __init__(self, strategy_obj: dict, fix_mode: str, **context):\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:65:        super().__init__(strategy_obj, **context)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:187:    \"\"\"Iterative javac fix strategy for version bump test repair.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:189:    def __init__(self, strategy_obj: dict, **context):\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:190:        super().__init__(strategy_obj, fix_mode=JAVA_FIX_MODE_JAVAC, **context)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:195:    \"\"\"Iterative java runtime fix strategy for version bump test repair.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:197:    def __init__(self, strategy_obj: dict, **context):\n../3312-20a114be/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:198:        super().__init__(strategy_obj, fix_mode=JAVA_FIX_MODE_JAVA_RUN, **context)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:263:        strategy_name,\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:275:    \"\"\"Build the PR body with metrics, strategy name, and optional stats.\"\"\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:305:- Strategy: {strategy_name}\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:313:- Iterations: {iterations}\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:403:    strategy_name = matched.get(\"strategy_name\", \"\")\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:404:    model_display_name = get_model_display_name(strategy_name)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:405:    agent_name = get_agent_name(strategy_name)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:417:        strategy_name=strategy_name,\n../