   \"description\": \"Benchmark suite for core libraries using baseline strategy.\",\n../3312-20a114be/forge/schemas/benchmark_suite_schema.json:52:        \"strategy\": \"baseline-iterative\"\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:83:        StratLoad[\"strategy_loader\"]\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:114:    Strategies -->|dispatch by name<br/>per strategy config| PostGen\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:159:strategy. They share a common skeleton: resolve paths and GraalVM, scaffold\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:160:the per-library directory, prepare source contexts, load the strategy, run\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:183:A predefined strategy names the agent it requires; the entry script\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:197:> class contract, per-strategy loop semantics, predefined-strategy bundles,\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:201:[`WorkflowStrategy`](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py)\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:208:| `basic_iterative` | [basic_iterative_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/basic_iterative_strategy.py) | Run-test → on failure, send error to agent → loop until pass or max iterations. |\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:209:| `dynamic_access_iterative` | [dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py) | Coverage-driven loop using the dynamic-access report; targets uncovered call sites. |\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:210:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | [optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py) | Variant of dynamic-access that primes coverage from source analysis. |\n../3312-20a114be/forge/docs/architecture.md:211:| `increase_dynamic_access_coverage` | [increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dyn